ABUJA – Disturbed by the terrible state of the environment in the six area councils of Abuja, the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) Minister of State, Dr. Ramatu Tijjani Aliyu, has ordered a thorough cleaning of all satellite towns in the nation’s capital. Aliyu, who gave the order takes immediate effect and will be overseen by the Coordinator of the Satellite Development Department (STDD), Comrade Obinna Francis Ogwuegbu, This, according to her is to ensure the immediate restoration of the environment for the safety of residents and the development of environmentally friendly communities. Ugwuanyi Mourns Anthony Obi Ochi’Idoma: OchetohaK’Idoma Sowing Seeds Of Discord… She stated that garbage generation in the FCT is increasing at an exponential rate as a result of the migration of Nigerians into the Capital Territory, as well as people’s attitudes, lifestyles, and environmental behaviors. Ogwuegbu has since hit the ground running after his inauguration to personally direct implementation and supervision of the Honourable Minister of State’s directive. It could be recalled that, the Coordinator, Satellite Town Development Department of the FCT, Comrade Obinna Francis Ogwuegbu has been on the trail of sanitary workers and has embarked on a massive clean up exercise around and within the six area Councils. The coordinator has assured residents of the FCT that the FCT administration remains committed to ensuring a safer and hygienic FCT for all residents. The coordinator who added that the exercise would be an ongoing one, appealed to residents, particularly those living in the suburbs to desist from dumping refuse in drainages and by the roadsides.